column3: 1. Days are counted from 1 (16 December 1944) to 32 (16
2. The sides are A (American), G (German), or B (British).
3. Unit abbreviations are as given in the source material.
Once a base unit was selected, its opposing units were
considered as engaged with it in proportion to the length of
their frontage which overlapped the frontage of the base
4. Strengths, losses, and other changes are for personnel,
and are assumed to be in proportion to the overlap of
frontages. Initial strengths are those at the start of the
day. Casualties and other changes are those that occurred
during that day. Total battle casualties include KIA, WIA,
POW, and MIA. Bloody casualties include only KIA and WIA.
Other changes are those not due to battle casualties.
5. The distance advanced is the distance the front moved
during the day. Distances are expressed from the viewpoint of
the Allies. That is, a negative value indicates that Allied
forces were moving backwards, and a positive value indicates
